HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1200
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Sergeant Jeremiah Cook
upon his receipt of the 2025 Supervisor of the
Year award.
WHEREAS, our nation was conceived by individuals who were willing to sacrifice their
personal concerns to ensure the public safety and welfare, and the Volunteer State is especially
proud to be the home of so many valiant individuals who have performed above and beyond the
call of duty in service of public safety; and
WHEREAS, Sergeant Jeremiah Cook is one such individual, who was recently honored
with the Chattanooga Police Department Supervisor of the Year award, in recognition of his
exemplary service as a servant leader; and
WHEREAS, Sergeant Jeremiah Cook, who currently serves as Rangemaster, is
routinely recognized as an exemplary officer and natural, positive leader who operates at a
much higher level of responsibility; and
WHEREAS, in 2025, Sergeant Cook personally spearheaded major overhauls of the
firing range, including adding firing lanes and a massive new rifle range; he designed, budgeted,
and partially hand-built the groundbreaking, state-of-the-art "shoot house"; and
WHEREAS, Sergeant Jeremiah Cook constantly innovates and implements streamlined
logistical changes for qualifications that have received universally positive feedback; and
WHEREAS, for a recent Medal of Honor celebration, Sergeant Cook coordinated city,
county, and outside contractors to help prepare the range property far beyond expectations; and
WHEREAS, the support and dedication provided by Sergeant Jeremiah Cook has made
a lasting impact on the Chattanooga Police Department; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
HJR1200
016033
- 1 -

CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Sergeant Jeremiah Cook upon his receipt of the
Supervisor of the Year award from the Chattanooga Police Department.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
- 2 - 016033

